Pending a hearing, the Commissioner may issue an order that prospectively suspends a rate filed by an insurer and reimposes the last previous rate in effect if the Commissioner has reasonable cause to believe that:
the rate is in violation of § 11-306 of this subtitle;
unless the order of suspension is issued, certain insureds will suffer irreparable harm;
the hardship that insureds will suffer in the absence of the order of suspension outweighs the hardship that the insurer would suffer if the order of suspension were issued; and
the order of suspension will not cause substantial harm to the public.

In determining the competitiveness of a market, the Commissioner shall consider all relevant factors including:
the number of insurers actively engaged in providing coverage in the market;
market shares;
changes in market shares; and
ease of entry.
